LUMPY SKIN DISEASE, BOVINE - TURKEY: (KAHRAMANMARAS) SUSPECTED, REQUEST FOR INFORMATION
***************************************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Sat 31 Aug 2013
Source: Sabah.com, Turkey [in Turkish, machine trans., summ., edited]
http://www.sabah.com.tr/Yasam/2013/08/31/sigir-olumlerindeki-korkutan-suphe


The Elbistan provincial Department of Food, Agriculture and Animal Husbandry suspects several cases of an exotic African disease of cattle, lumpy skin disease, in the village Catova.

It is believed that the disease has been introduced by smuggling of cattle from Middle Eastern countries such as Syria and Iraq. Blood and skin samples have been obtained and sent to a veterinary research institute for laboratory diagnosis. Measures are being undertaken by the authorities to control the disease and prevent its spread to other villages.

According to the director of the District Food, Agriculture and Livestock Directorate, Recep Yilmaz, this African disease, which can be spread by flies, has never been seen before in Turkey.

--
Communicated by:
Sabine Zentis
